{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":960,"text":"Let me tell you a story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2968,"text":"It's my first year as a new\nhigh school science teacher,"},{"time":6739,"text":"and I'm so eager."},{"time":8527,"text":"I'm so excited, I'm pouring\nmyself into my lesson plans."},{"time":13693,"text":"But I'm slowly coming\nto this horrifying realization"},{"time":18550,"text":"that my students just might\nnot be learning anything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23605,"text":"This happens one day:"},{"time":25336,"text":"I'd just assigned my class\nto read this textbook chapter"},{"time":28494,"text":"about my favorite subject\nin all of biology:"},{"time":32235,"text":"viruses and how they attack."},{"time":35727,"text":"And so I'm so excited\nto discuss this with them,"},{"time":38079,"text":"and I come in and I say,\n\"Can somebody please explain"},{"time":41450,"text":"the main ideas and why this is so cool?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":45812,"text":"There's silence."},{"time":49352,"text":"Finally, my favorite student,\nshe looks me straight in the eye,"},{"time":52336,"text":"and she says, \"The reading sucked.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":55257,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":57525,"text":"And then she clarified."},{"time":58844,"text":"She said, \"You know what,\nI don't mean that it sucks."},{"time":61367,"text":"I mean I didn't understand a word of it."},{"time":63429,"text":"It's boring, who cares, and it sucks.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":67453,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":69333,"text":"These sympathetic smiles\nspread all throughout the room now,"},{"time":74223,"text":"and I realize that all of my other\nstudents are in the same boat,"},{"time":79056,"text":"that maybe they took notes or memorized\ndefinitions from the textbook,"},{"time":82968,"text":"but not one of them\nreally understood the main ideas."},{"time":88071,"text":"Not one of them can tell me\nwhy this stuff is so cool,"},{"time":90745,"text":"why it's so important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94237,"text":"I'm totally clueless."},{"time":96181,"text":"I have no idea what to do next."},{"time":99451,"text":"So the only thing I can think of is say,"},{"time":102387,"text":"\"Listen. Let me tell you a story."},{"time":106306,"text":"The main characters in the story\nare bacteria and viruses."},{"time":112355,"text":"These guys are blown up\na couple million times."},{"time":115831,"text":"The real bacteria and viruses are so small"},{"time":118997,"text":"we can't see them without a microscope,"},{"time":121275,"text":"and you guys might know\nbacteria and viruses"},{"time":123409,"text":"because they both make us sick."},{"time":125536,"text":"But what a lot of people don't know"},{"time":127456,"text":"is that viruses\ncan also make bacteria sick.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":132059,"text":"Now, the story\nthat I start telling my kids,"},{"time":134559,"text":"it starts out like a horror story."},{"time":138887,"text":"Once upon a time,\nthere's this happy little bacterium."},{"time":142490,"text":"Don't get too attached to him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143981,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":145697,"text":"Maybe he's floating around in your stomach"},{"time":148387,"text":"or in some spoiled food somewhere,"},{"time":150585,"text":"and all of a sudden,\nhe starts to not feel so good."},{"time":154213,"text":"Maybe he ate something bad for lunch."},{"time":156815,"text":"And then things get really horrible,"},{"time":159378,"text":"as his skin rips apart,"},{"time":160999,"text":"and he sees a virus\ncoming out from his insides."},{"time":165505,"text":"And then it gets horrible\nwhen he bursts open"},{"time":169075,"text":"and an army of viruses\nfloods out from his insides."},{"time":174636,"text":"\"Ouch\" is right."},{"time":177643,"text":"If you see this, and you're a bacterium,"},{"time":180191,"text":"this is like your worst nightmare."},{"time":183413,"text":"But if you're a virus and you see this,"},{"time":185793,"text":"you cross those little legs\nof yours and you think,"},{"time":188833,"text":"\"We rock.\""},{"time":190729,"text":"Because it took a lot of crafty work\nto infect this bacterium."},{"time":196170,"text":"Here's what had to happen."},{"time":197987,"text":"A virus grabbed onto a bacterium"},{"time":201193,"text":"and it slipped its DNA into it."},{"time":204803,"text":"The next thing\nis that virus DNA made stuff"},{"time":208184,"text":"that chopped up the bacteria DNA."},{"time":212445,"text":"And now that we've gotten rid\nof the bacteria DNA,"},{"time":214905,"text":"the virus DNA takes control of the cell"},{"time":218734,"text":"and it tells it to start\nmaking more viruses."},{"time":223353,"text":"Because, you see, DNA is like a blueprint"},{"time":226559,"text":"that tells living things what to make."},{"time":230163,"text":"So this is kind of like going\ninto a car factory"},{"time":233567,"text":"and replacing the blueprints\nwith blueprints for killer robots."},{"time":239265,"text":"The workers still come\nthe next day, they do their job,"},{"time":242233,"text":"but they're following\ndifferent instructions."},{"time":245524,"text":"So replacing the bacteria\nDNA with virus DNA"},{"time":249301,"text":"turns the bacteria into a factory\nfor making viruses --"},{"time":254147,"text":"that is, until it's so filled\nwith viruses that it bursts."},{"time":258896,"text":"But that's not the only way\nthat viruses infect bacteria."},{"time":262825,"text":"Some are much more crafty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266307,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":268991,"text":"When a secret agent virus\ninfects a bacterium,"},{"time":273800,"text":"they do a little espionage."},{"time":276235,"text":"Here, this cloaked, secret agent virus"},{"time":280360,"text":"is slipping his DNA\ninto the bacterial cell,"},{"time":283147,"text":"but here's the kicker:"},{"time":284766,"text":"It doesn't do anything\nharmful -- not at first."},{"time":289043,"text":"Instead, it silently slips\ninto the bacteria's own DNA,"},{"time":294622,"text":"and it just stays there\nlike a terrorist sleeper cell,"},{"time":299344,"text":"waiting for instructions."},{"time":302214,"text":"And what's interesting about this is now,\nwhenever this bacteria has babies,"},{"time":307936,"text":"the babies also have\nthe virus DNA in them."},{"time":313753,"text":"So now we have a whole\nextended bacteria family,"},{"time":317610,"text":"filled with virus sleeper cells."},{"time":321106,"text":"They're just happily living together\nuntil a signal happens"},{"time":325875,"text":"and bam! -- all of the DNA pops out."},{"time":330343,"text":"It takes control of these cells,\nturns them into virus-making factories,"},{"time":334009,"text":"and they all burst,"},{"time":335825,"text":"a huge, extended bacteria family,"},{"time":338547,"text":"all dying with viruses\nspilling out of their guts,"},{"time":341692,"text":"the viruses taking over the bacterium."},{"time":346660,"text":"So now you understand\nhow viruses can attack cells."},{"time":350755,"text":"There are two ways:"},{"time":352383,"text":"On the left is what we call the lytic way,"},{"time":355366,"text":"where the viruses go right in\nand take over the cells."},{"time":359278,"text":"On the [right] is the lysogenic way"},{"time":362373,"text":"that uses secret agent viruses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365944,"text":"So this stuff is not that hard, right?"},{"time":368222,"text":"And now all of you understand it."},{"time":370245,"text":"But if you've graduated from high school,"},{"time":372260,"text":"I can almost guarantee\nyou've seen this information before."},{"time":375546,"text":"But I bet it was presented in a way\nthat it didn't exactly stick in your mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382119,"text":"So when my students\nwere first learning this,"},{"time":385611,"text":"why did they hate it so much?"},{"time":387952,"text":"Well, there were a couple of reasons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390110,"text":"First of all, I can guarantee you"},{"time":392285,"text":"you that their textbooks\ndidn't have secret agent viruses,"},{"time":395691,"text":"and they didn't have horror stories."},{"time":398680,"text":"You know, in the communication of science,"},{"time":401410,"text":"there is this obsession with seriousness."},{"time":405458,"text":"It kills me. I'm not kidding."},{"time":407584,"text":"I used to work\nfor an educational publisher,"},{"time":409837,"text":"and as a writer, I was always told\nnever to use stories"},{"time":413520,"text":"or fun, engaging language,"},{"time":415432,"text":"because then my work might not be viewed\nas \"serious\" and \"scientific.\""},{"time":420848,"text":"I mean, because God\nforbid somebody have fun"},{"time":423943,"text":"when they're learning science."},{"time":425735,"text":"So we have this field of science\nthat's all about slime"},{"time":430597,"text":"and color changes."},{"time":432964,"text":"Check this out."},{"time":444496,"text":"And then we have, of course,\nas any good scientist has to have ..."},{"time":449115,"text":"explosions!"},{"time":451903,"text":"But if a textbook seems too much fun,"},{"time":456593,"text":"it's somehow unscientific."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460511,"text":"Now another problem"},{"time":463338,"text":"was that the language in their textbook\nwas truly incomprehensible."},{"time":469718,"text":"If we want to summarize that story\nthat I told you earlier,"},{"time":472527,"text":"we could start by saying,"},{"time":473837,"text":"\"These viruses make copies of themselves"},{"time":476003,"text":"by slipping their DNA into a bacterium.\""},{"time":479003,"text":"The way this showed up in the textbook,\nit looked like this:"},{"time":482368,"text":"\"Bacteriophage replication is initiated"},{"time":485606,"text":"through the introduction of viral\nnucleic acid into a bacterium.\""},{"time":490965,"text":"That's great, perfect for 13-year-olds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":496052,"text":"But here's the thing:"},{"time":497257,"text":"There are plenty of people\nin science education"},{"time":499831,"text":"who would look\nat this and say there's no way"},{"time":502011,"text":"that we could ever give that to students,"},{"time":504452,"text":"because it contains some language\nthat isn't completely accurate."},{"time":509666,"text":"For example, I told you\nthat viruses have DNA."},{"time":512523,"text":"Well, a very tiny fraction of them don't."},{"time":515150,"text":"They have something called RNA instead."},{"time":517465,"text":"So a professional science writer\nwould say, \"That has to go."},{"time":520791,"text":"We have to change it to something\nmuch more technical.\""},{"time":523405,"text":"And after a team\nof professional science editors"},{"time":526157,"text":"went over this really simple explanation,"},{"time":529990,"text":"they'd find fault\nwith almost every word I've used,"},{"time":534418,"text":"and they'd have to change anything\nthat wasn't serious enough,"},{"time":537347,"text":"and they'd have to change everything"},{"time":539086,"text":"that wasn't 100 percent perfect."},{"time":542544,"text":"Then it would be accurate,"},{"time":544432,"text":"but it would be completely\nimpossible to understand."},{"time":549305,"text":"This is horrifying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551553,"text":"You know, I keep talking\nabout this idea of telling a story,"},{"time":556446,"text":"and it's like science communication\nhas taken on this idea"},{"time":561041,"text":"of what I call the tyranny of precision,"},{"time":564120,"text":"where you can't just tell a story."},{"time":566275,"text":"It's like science has become\nthat horrible storyteller that we all know"},{"time":571917,"text":"who gives us all the details\nnobody cares about,"},{"time":574536,"text":"where you're like, \"Oh, I met\nmy friend for lunch the other day,"},{"time":578385,"text":"and she was wearing these ugly jeans."},{"time":580202,"text":"I mean, they weren't really jeans,\nthey were more like leggings,"},{"time":583226,"text":"but I guess they're actually\nkind of more like jeggings,"},{"time":585884,"text":"and you're just like,\n\"Oh my God. What is the point?\""},{"time":590776,"text":"Or even worse,\nscience education is becoming"},{"time":594760,"text":"like that guy who always says, \"Actually.\""},{"time":598735,"text":"You want to be like,"},{"time":600615,"text":"\"Oh, dude, we had to get up\nin the middle of the night"},{"time":603750,"text":"and drive a hundred miles\nin total darkness.\""},{"time":606456,"text":"And that guy's like,\n\"Actually, it was 87.3 miles.\""},{"time":611138,"text":"And you're like, \"Actually, shut up!\nI'm just trying to tell a story.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":618471,"text":"Because good storytelling\nis all about emotional connection."},{"time":624010,"text":"We have to convince our audience"},{"time":626561,"text":"that what we're talking about matters."},{"time":629545,"text":"But just as important is knowing\nwhich details we should leave out"},{"time":634800,"text":"so that the main point still comes across."},{"time":638279,"text":"I'm reminded of what the architect\nMies van der Rohe said,"},{"time":641286,"text":"and I paraphrase,\nwhen he said that sometimes,"},{"time":644675,"text":"you have to lie\nin order to tell the truth."},{"time":648238,"text":"I think this sentiment is particularly\nrelevant to science education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654952,"text":"Now, finally, I am often so disappointed"},{"time":661742,"text":"when people think that I'm advocating\na dumbing down of science."},{"time":666948,"text":"That's not true at all."},{"time":668646,"text":"I'm currently a Ph.D. student at MIT,"},{"time":671447,"text":"and I absolutely understand\nthe importance of detailed,"},{"time":676453,"text":"specific scientific\ncommunication between experts,"},{"time":681346,"text":"but not when we're trying\nto teach 13-year-olds."},{"time":685856,"text":"If a young learner\nthinks that all viruses have DNA,"},{"time":690952,"text":"that's not going to ruin\ntheir chances of success in science."},{"time":696466,"text":"But if a young learner\ncan't understand anything in science"},{"time":700045,"text":"and learns to hate it because it\nall sounds like this,"},{"time":704004,"text":"that will ruin their chances of success."}]},{"cues":[{"time":708765,"text":"This needs to stop ..."},{"time":711118,"text":"and I wish that the change could come\nfrom the institutions at the top"},{"time":714936,"text":"that are perpetuating these problems,"},{"time":716722,"text":"and I beg them,\nI beseech them to just stop it."},{"time":721528,"text":"But I think that's unlikely."},{"time":723509,"text":"So we are so lucky that we have resources"},{"time":727072,"text":"like the Internet, where we can\ncircumvent these institutions"},{"time":730230,"text":"from the bottom up."},{"time":733593,"text":"There's a growing number\nof online resources"},{"time":736505,"text":"that are dedicated\nto just explaining science"},{"time":739831,"text":"in simple, understandable ways."},{"time":742934,"text":"I dream of a Wikipedia-like website"},{"time":745314,"text":"that would explain\nany scientific concept you can think of"},{"time":749037,"text":"in simple language\nany middle schooler can understand."},{"time":753521,"text":"And I myself spend most of my free time"},{"time":756989,"text":"making these science videos\nthat I put on YouTube."},{"time":760613,"text":"I explain chemical equilibrium"},{"time":762847,"text":"using analogies to awkward\nmiddle school dances,"},{"time":766351,"text":"and I talk about fuel cells"},{"time":768081,"text":"with stories about boys and girls\nat a summer camp."},{"time":772246,"text":"The feedback that I get\nis sometimes misspelled"},{"time":775674,"text":"and it's often written in LOLcats,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":777841,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":779079,"text":"but nonetheless,\nit's so appreciative, so thankful"},{"time":785023,"text":"that I know this is the right way\nwe should be communicating science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792073,"text":"There's still so much work\nleft to be done, though,"},{"time":795144,"text":"and if you're involved\nwith science in any way,"},{"time":798406,"text":"I urge you to join me."},{"time":801096,"text":"Pick up a camera, start\nto write a blog, whatever,"},{"time":806480,"text":"but leave out the seriousness,\nleave out the jargon."},{"time":810329,"text":"Make me laugh. Make me care."},{"time":813724,"text":"Leave out those annoying details\nthat nobody cares about"},{"time":817303,"text":"and just get to the point."},{"time":821049,"text":"How should you start?"},{"time":822914,"text":"Why don't you say,\n\"Listen, let me tell you a story.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":828063,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}